You are right here.
No, you are right there.

00:28:39.652 --> 00:28:43.166
Recitation eight,
what is the definition of the

00:28:43.166 --> 00:28:45.000
electron affinity?

00:28:50.000 --> 00:28:55.857
TAs cannot help.
Energy required to add an

00:28:55.857 --> 00:28:59.000
electron, that is --

00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:12.604
Recitation eight,
you are right.

00:29:12.604 --> 00:29:16.093
It is minus delta E.
Fantastic.

00:29:16.093 --> 00:29:20.046
This is the delta E for the
reason.

00:29:20.046 --> 00:29:25.162
The electron affinity is minus
that quantity.

00:29:25.162 --> 00:29:30.511
The electron affinity,
then, of chlorine is 349

00:29:30.511 --> 00:29:36.770
kilojoules per mole.
Now, unlike the ionization

00:29:36.770 --> 00:29:42.844
energy, the electron affinity
can be positive or negative.

00:29:42.844 --> 00:29:47.426
For example,
if you try to stick an electron

00:29:47.426 --> 00:29:52.114
on a nitrogen atom to make N
minus,

00:29:52.114 --> 00:29:56.057
delta E for that reaction is
positive.

00:29:56.057 --> 00:30:02.882
It is 7 kilojoules per mole.
And so that electron is not

00:30:02.882 --> 00:30:06.298
going to stick onto the
nitrogen.

00:30:06.298 --> 00:30:11.209
The electron affinity in that
case is negative.

00:30:11.209 --> 00:30:14.733
It is minus 7 kilojoules per
mole.

00:30:14.733 --> 00:30:20.498
Again, you can understand that
in terms of the electron

00:30:20.498 --> 00:30:25.943
configuration for the nitrogen.
Here is the electron

00:30:25.943 --> 00:30:32.279
configuration for nitrogen.
If you go and you want to add

00:30:32.279 --> 00:30:35.186
in another electron,
like right there,

00:30:35.186 --> 00:30:37.701
there is a repulsive
interaction.

00:30:37.701 --> 00:30:39.902
And Z equals 7.
In this case,

00:30:39.902 --> 00:30:44.303
that nuclear charge is not
large enough to compensate for

00:30:44.303 --> 00:30:48.390
this repulsive interaction,
so the electron affinity,

00:30:48.390 --> 00:30:51.769
here, is negative.
Noble gases have negative

00:30:51.769 --> 00:30:55.620
electron affinities.
You cannot add an electron to

00:30:55.620 --> 00:30:57.349
that.
It is not stable.

00:30:57.349 --> 00:31:02.623
Why?
Because you are destroying,

00:31:02.623 --> 00:31:10.004
in effect, the electronic
configuration of the rare gas.

00:31:10.004 --> 00:31:17.116
With that, now we want to ask
is how does the electron

00:31:17.116 --> 00:31:23.961
